## Private Member Functions

### findValue() {#a45c01fee2a4739a577e0c00ab5606252}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Value &#42; Lint::findValue (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> &#42; V, bool OffsetOk) const</>}>
findValue - Look through bitcasts and simple memory reference patterns to identify an equivalent, but more informative, value.

If OffsetOk is true, look through getelementptrs with non-zero offsets too.

Most analysis passes don&#39;t require this logic, because instcombine will simplify most of these kinds of things away. But it&#39;s a goal of this <a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-lint-cpp-/lint">Lint</a> pass to be useful even on non-optimized IR.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/lint-cpp/#l00124">124</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/lint-cpp">Lint.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
